About this hotel

Close to restaurants, this homey hotel is 2 km from Jemaa el-Fnaa, a bustling square and marketplace in Marrakesh's Medina (old city). It's 7 km from Marrakech Menara Airport.

Check-in time: 2:30 PM
Check-out time: 12:30 PM

    Natasha Gillies3 years ago on Google
    4/5
    I stayed in this riad for 2 nights with a friend. The rooms are comfortable, clean, and decorated nicely in traditional Moroccan decor with a fossil-theme. However it may be worth knowing that the riad is very close to a mosque, and you may …
    I stayed in this riad for 2 nights with a friend. The rooms are comfortable, clean, and decorated nicely in traditional Moroccan decor with a fossil-theme. However it may be worth knowing that the riad is very close to a mosque, and you may be woken by the call to prayer in the morning - our room directly faced one of the loudspeakers, and both mornings we were woken at 6am by the call which lasted for 20 minutes. If you're a light sleeper ear plugs may help. The riad has a beautiful terrace which features numerous sun loungers and a jacuzzi - though be warned it is ice cold. We missed breakfast the first day as we got in late and slept through it. On the second, we had to leave at 7:30 for an excursion. As breakfast began at 7 we didn't think this would be a problem, but from when we got downstairs to when we left they were serving only cold, sliced white bread and jam which was very disappointing. The riad is a little bit out of the way, though it doesn't take long to find yourself back on the main souks, I didn't feel very relaxed walking about on my own. The staff are friendly and approachable, and were good at giving us directions to nearby places.

    Medina

    Hammam bath houses and covered spice and textile souks line the maze of cobblestoned lanes in the Medina, which occupies Marrakesh’s original fortified citadel. At night, Jemaa el-Fna square teems with snake charmers, folk dancers, and street food vendors serving all manner of food. Bahia Palace and Le Jardin Secret are 19th-century complexes open to the public, with ornate courtyards, mosaics, and gardens.

    About this hotel

    Close to restaurants, this homey hotel is 2 km from Jemaa el-Fnaa, a bustling square and marketplace in Marrakesh's Medina (old city). It's 7 km from Marrakech Menara Airport. …

    Polished rooms with traditional Moroccan decor feature free Wi-Fi, satellite TV, safes and minibars, as well as balconies, terraces or patios. Room service is available.

    Complimentary breakfast is served in a relaxed restaurant. Other amenities include indoor and outdoor pools, plus a rooftop terrace and a gym. There’s also a beauty salon and a spa, which has a hammam and a hot tub. Parking is available.
